<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-486-458  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 486 458.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  May 28 1990 v12 n22 pS1(6).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Windows 3.0: worth the wait. (in-depth analysis of MicrosoftWindows 3.0 graphical user interface)(includes related article onbundled accessory programs)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Miller, Michael J.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A detailed technical description of Microsoft's new Windows 3.0graphical user interface is presented.andP;  Windows 3.0 has a moreattractive user interface than previous versions, uses theprotected mode features of the 286 and 386 processors, andprovides multitasking and support for extended memory.andP;  Theprogram requires a fast 286- or 386-based microcomputer with2Mbytes of RAM for acceptable performance.andP;  It can run in 'real'mode, which needs 640Kbytes of memory and is similar to theoperation of earlier Windows versions; 'standard' mode, whichrequires a 286 with 1Mbyte of RAM and takes advantage of extendedmemory; and 'enhanced' mode, which requires a 386 with 2Mbytes andhas sophisticated memory management features and allowsmultitasking of non-Windows applications.andP;  Non-Windows programsrun in the 386 chip's 'virtual 86' mode.andP;  Most applicationsdesigned for Windows 2.0 will not work with Windows 3.0, but mostmajor vendors will release free or inexpensive upgrades within afew months.andP;  The 386 enhanced mode's memory management scheme isincompatible with today's DOS extenders.andP;  The program lets userswork with multiple applications simultaneously; applications canfill the screen.andP;  A new graphical set-up program automaticallydetermines the user's hardware configuration and installs theproper files, placing applications it recognizes into 'programgroups.' All Windows applications use a common 'clipboard' forexchanging data and support Dynamic Data Exchange for hot linking.andO;Users can customize the Windows 3.0 environment extensively.andO;Other major new features in Windows 3.0 include LAN support andhypertext-style help.andP;  The program comes bundled with a paintprogram, several accessories and a macro recorder.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (products).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   Microsoft Windows 3.0 (Graphical user interface) (design andconstruction).andO;Topic:     Graphical User InterfaceOperating EnvironmentsSoftware DesignNew Product.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>